## Performance Errors

In the very first stages of the code, where we had the rover working, the car would barely work and needed multiple adjustments.

The very first thing that needed adjusted was the speed of the motors.
When the car was told to just go straight, it would curve to the left roughly 40 degrees over a 3 second period.
This means, that the right motor was spinning faster than the left motor.
In order to fix this, we implimented an adjustment to the speeds so the code could make up for the mis-match.
Origianlly, we implimented a trim on the right motor, which would make the right motor spin less and match the left.
This worked at first and would drive relativly striaght, however, the wheel would occasionally quit spinning.
The cause we found for this was the friction in the gearbox would slow down the wheel if the speed was too low. 
The new solution we came up with was to increase the speed of the left wheel in order to match the right wheel.
This is very similar to the trim, however it is just the opposite. 
